<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "2C">
<servcat sctnbr = "02" scnbr = "03">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B2306007" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Rear Axle Removal and Installation
</title>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Brake fluid is extremely damaging to painted surfaces. If brake fluid contacts painted surface, immediately wipe it off and flush the surface with water thoroughly.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Rear axle bolts are pre-coated with friction stabilizer. Do not reuse rear axle bolt, otherwise bolts may loosen.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B2306007001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle and remove rear wheels.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear brake backing plate or rear brake disc dust cover and caliper for each of right and left rear wheel.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Drum brake model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4316009"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Disc brake model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4326005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove wheel speed sensor clamp (4), rear wheel speed sensor harness (5) and parking brake cable clamp (6) from each of right and left rear axle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rear wheel speed sensor for each of right and left rear wheel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4606008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
 / 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect brake pipes (1) from brake hoses (2), and then remove E-ring (3) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A230014.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "168.293mm" ver = "02" gw = "233" gh = "461"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.129in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.129in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Disc brake model
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[B]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Dram brake model
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect shock absorber lower end from rear axle and remove coil springs.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Rear shock absorber: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Rear coil spring: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2306005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
While supporting rear axle at both ends, remove tailing arm bolts (1), and then remove rear axle from vehicle body by lowering floor jack gradually.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A230008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "52.902mm" ver = "02" gw = "217" gh = "130"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B2306007002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Place rear axle on floor jacks.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Then install rear axle with new right and left rear axle bolts (1) and tighten bolts temporarily by hand.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A230008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "52.902mm" ver = "02" gw = "217" gh = "130"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install coil spring and connect shock absorber lower end to rear axle. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect brake pipes to brake hoses, and then install E-rings. Tighten rear brake pipe flare nuts to specified torque. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4106012"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install wheel speed sensor clamp and parking brake cable clamp to rear axle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear wheel speed sensor and parking brake cable for each of right and left rear wheels.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Rear wheel speed sensor (ABS model): 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4506008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Rear wheel speed sensor (ESP<sup>&#174;</sup> model): 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4606008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Parking brake cable: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear brake back plate or rear brake disc dust cover and caliper for each of right and left rear wheels.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Drum brake model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4316009"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Disc brake model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4326005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
After installing brake parts, bleed air from brake system. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4106004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Adjust parking brake. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B4406002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install rear wheels. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2406001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Lower hoist and bounce vehicle up and down several times to stabilize suspension.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten rear shock absorber lower nuts and rear axle bolts to specified torques. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B2306003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Tighten rear axle bolts to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T2C004">
<t-part>
Rear axle bolt
</t-part>
<t-value1>
73
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
7.4
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
54.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that rear brake are free from dragging and proper braking is obtained.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check all installed parts for brake fluid leakage.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
